properties.areaDesc: Inner Channels from Kupreanof Island to Etolin Island
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 29 at 3:19PM AKST until January 30 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Juneau has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect from 6 AM to noon AKST Thursday. The
High Wind Watch is no longer in effect.

* WHAT...South winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph.


* WHERE...Portions of the central Inner Channels including Kake,
Coffman Cove, Point Baker.

* WHEN...From Thursday morning through Thursday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are possible. Improperly moored boats
and aircraft may break loose from their tie-downs.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A high wind warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO NOON AKST THURSDAY
